displayAddress: Unit 10 Park Hill, South Street, Sheffield, South Yorkshire
detailedDescription: Park Hill is a Brutalist, concrete icon, and the largest listed building in Europe. Standing proudly at the top of hill overlooking Sheffield city centre Park Hill was a utopian vision, created in 1961 to create a new community for families. Its distinctive 'streets in the sky' - spaces outside each home that were wide enough for a milk float to do doorstep deliveries - were places in which families congregated and life thrived. Fast forward to 2023, and Park Hill is that place once more, re-imagined, re-invigorated and regenerated. The Sunday Times recently cited Park Hill as somewhere helping to make Sheffield the 'Capital of Cool'. The units are finished to a shell specification with capped services. This will allow occupier(s) to fit the space(s) out to reflect their businesses and personalities. Importance of "Community" Key to Urban Splash is the creation of "a community" at Park Hill. Part of this is having great people in the workspaces such as The Pearl, South Street Kitchen, the Grace Owen Nursery, Human, Warp Films, Airship, Alpha Recruitment, Content OD, Pukator, Kada Research, AAD Architects, Can Studios, 12 Miles North and Hive IT. Park Hill also proudly accommodates the social enterprise, S1 Art Gallery. So you can see, Park Hill is very much a continuing story... why not make your business part of it? The units are finished to a shell specification with capped services. This will allow occupier(s) to fit the space(s) out to reflect their businesses and personalities.
